Extreme Paintbrawl 2 is the sequel to Extreme Paintbrawl. It was released for Microsoft Windows on November 15, 1999. The game uses a modified version of the Genesis 3D engine, and is considered by many to be one of the worst video games of all time.

== Criticism ==
Extreme Paintbrawl 2 has been considered by many to be one of the worst video games ever made. It is also said that the game has abysmal AI, as the player's teammates constantly run into walls and get stuck anywhere possible. IGN gave the game a score of 2.6/10, as for the original Extreme Paintbrawl, IGN gave it a 0.7/10, which is the third lowest rated game on the website.

